DataElement.preferredDefinition: Examination of the body by auscultation, palpation, percussion, inspection, and olfaction.  (Taber's)_The system of muscles, tendons, ligaments, bones, joints and associated tissues that move the body and maintain its form.:A systemic evaluation of the body and its functions using visual inspection, palpation, percussion, and auscultation, aimed to determine the presence or absence of physical signs of disease or abnormality for individual's health assessment._Generic value domain for a primitive java dataype that is an Integer (32-bit two's complement).
